---
const steps = [
	{ label: 'Pattern', sub: '2-2-3 · week-on/week-off · every-other-weekend', active: true },
	{ label: 'Start date', sub: 'Anchor week one to first exchange Monday', active: false },
	{ label: 'Month grid', sub: 'Color-coded nights + exchange stripes', active: false },
	{ label: 'PDF export', sub: 'Printable calendar + exhibit cover', active: false },
];
---

<figure class="calendar-construction w-full max-w-full overflow-hidden rounded-[1.25rem] border border-line bg-surface/50 p-4 sm:p-5 shadow-[inset_0_0_0_1px_var(--border-subtle)]">
	<figcaption class="text-sm font-semibold tracking-[-0.02em] text-primary sm:text-base">
		Calendar construction — pattern to printable PDF
	</figcaption>
	<p class="mt-2 text-xs leading-5 text-secondary sm:text-sm sm:leading-6">
		Each step feeds the next: pick rotation, set anchor date, preview months, export.
	</p>

	<div class="mt-5 flex flex-col items-center gap-1 sm:flex-row sm:flex-wrap sm:justify-center">
		{steps.map((step, i) => (
			<>
				<div
					class:list={[
						'w-full rounded-lg px-3 py-2.5 sm:w-auto sm:min-w-[120px]',
						step.active
							? 'bg-accent/15 ring-2 ring-accent/40'
							: 'bg-surface ring-1 ring-line-subtle',
					]}
				>
					<p class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary">{step.label}</p>
					<p class="mt-0.5 text-[10px] leading-4 text-secondary">{step.sub}</p>
				</div>
				{i < steps.length - 1 && (
					<span class="text-muted sm:px-1" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
				)}
			</>
		))}
	</div>

	<p class="mt-4 text-center text-[11px] leading-5 text-muted">
		Holiday overrides apply after the base grid is built — they replace nights, not the pattern picker
	</p>
</figure>
